name: ecommerce-seo-performance
description: Enforce SEO and performance best practices for production e-commerce
alwaysApply: true

rules:

  # URL & Routing
  - All public pages MUST use clean, keyword-based URLs.
  - NEVER use query parameters for product pages.
  - Product URLs MUST follow: /products/{product-slug}
  - Product list: /products (no category filtering).

  # Meta & Indexing
  - Every indexable page MUST include:
      - Unique <title> (50–60 chars)
      - Unique meta description (140–160 chars)
      - Canonical URL
  - Duplicate meta tags are NOT allowed.

  # Headings
  - Each page MUST contain exactly ONE <h1>.
  - <h1> MUST reflect the primary search intent.
  - Headings MUST follow hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3).

  # Product Content
  - Product pages MUST contain:
      - Minimum 300 words of original content
      - Use-case descriptions
      - FAQ section
  - Manufacturer copy-paste is FORBIDDEN.

  # Images
  - All images MUST:
      - Use WebP or AVIF
      - Include descriptive alt text
      - Be lazy-loaded if non-critical

  # Structured Data
  - Product pages MUST include:
      - Product schema
      - Offer schema (price, availability)
      - Review schema (if available)

  # Performance
  - SSR is REQUIRED for SEO-critical pages.
  - JavaScript must be code-split.
  - No blocking scripts allowed.

  # Internal Linking
  - Product pages MUST link to:
      - Products list (/products)
      - Related products where available
  - Orphan pages are NOT allowed.

  # Crawl Control
  - Filter URLs MUST be noindex.
  - Internal search pages MUST be noindex.
